Now comes a serious demand, an absolute injunction. Never, never--atleast while I am still alive--never, I repeat, shall you try to communicatewith the child. I do not know--Nelly is better versed in this--what thelegal situation is, but I know that in certain respects you are a gentlemanand it is to the gentleman that I say and shout: Please, please, keep away!If some dreadful American illness strikes me, then remember I wish her to bebrought up as a